---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout 
    title="Documentation" 
    description="Learn how to use Basis Stack to build modern web applications"
>
    <div class="space-y-8">
        <section>
            <h2 id="getting-started">Getting Started</h2>
            <p>
                Welcome to the Basis Stack documentation. This guide will help you get up and running
                with our modern web development stack that combines Astro, Alpine.js, and Supabase.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
            <p>
                Basis Stack provides a complete solution for building dynamic web applications with:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Astro</strong> - Fast, content-focused web framework</li>
                <li><strong>Alpine.js</strong> - Lightweight JavaScript framework for reactivity</li>
                <li><strong>Supabase</strong> - Open source Firebase alternative</li>
                <li><strong>Tailwind CSS</strong> - Utility-first CSS framework</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 id="quick-start">Quick Start</h2>
            <p>Get started with Basis Stack in just a few steps:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Clone the repository</li>
                <li>Install dependencies with <code>npm install</code></li>
                <li>Configure your environment variables</li>
                <li>Run <code>npm run dev</code> to start the development server</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 id="features">Features</h2>
            <p>Basis Stack comes with everything you need:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Complete UI component library</li>
                <li>Authentication with Supabase</li>
                <li>Real-time database</li>
                <li>Dark mode support</li>
                <li>TypeScript support</li>
                <li>SEO optimized</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </div>
</DocsLayout>